[[File:Dumping_of_faecal_sludge_into_the_river.jpg|thumb]][[内罗毕|内罗毕]]]]
导致疾病的[[微生物|微生物]]被称之为[[病原体|病原体]]。虽然大多数细菌既不致病也没用处，但一些细菌会导致疾病。大肠型细菌虽然不会导致疾病，但常被用作水污染细菌指标。其它在地表水出现的微生物有时也会致病，如：
* ''[[类鼻疽伯克氏菌|类鼻疽伯克氏菌]]''
* ''[[小隐孢子虫|小隐孢子虫]]''
* ''[[兰氏贾第鞭毛虫|蓝氏贾第鞭毛虫]]''
* ''[[沙门氏菌属|沙门氏菌属]]''
* ''[[诺如病毒|诺如病毒]]''及其它病毒
* ''[[寄生虫|寄生虫]]，包括[[血吸虫|血吸虫]]类型 <ref>USGS. Reston, VA. [http://pubs.usgs.gov/fs/fs-027-01/ "A Primer on Water Quality."] {{Wayback|url=http://pubs.usgs.gov/fs/fs-027-01/ |date=20170728013800 }} FS-027-01. March 2001.</ref><ref>Schueler, Thomas R. "Microbes and Urban Watersheds: Concentrations, Sources, & Pathways." Reprinted in [http://cwp.org/documents/cat_view/75-articles-from-the-practice-of-watershed-protection.html?limit=40&order=name&dir=DESC&start=80 ''The Practice of Watershed Protection.''] {{Wayback|url=http://cwp.org/documents/cat_view/75-articles-from-the-practice-of-watershed-protection.html?limit=40&order=name&dir=DESC&start=80 |date=20130108194041 }} 2000. Center for Watershed Protection. Ellicott City, MD.</ref>

高浓度病原体可能来自就地卫生系统（[[化粪池|化粪池]]、[[旱厕|旱厕]]）或排放未经足够处理的污水。<ref>EPA. [http://www.epa.gov/npdes/sso/control/diseases.htm “Illness Related to Sewage in Water.”]Accessed February 20, 2009. {{Wayback|url=http://www.epa.gov/npdes/sso/control/diseases.htm |date=20060427093431 }}</ref>这也可能是污水处理厂二级处理不佳所致（多发生在欠发达国家）。在发达国家，老城破旧的污水系统泄露（管道、泵、阀门）会导致卫生下水系统满溢。有的城市有合流下水系统，会因雨水冲刷而排放未经处理的污水。<ref name="EPARTC">EPA. "[https://www.epa.gov/npdes/2004-npdes-cso-report-congress Report to Congress: Impacts and Control of CSOs and SSOs."] {{Wayback|url=https://www.epa.gov/npdes/2004-npdes-cso-report-congress |date=20200623062228 }} August 2004. Document No. EPA-833-R-04-001.</ref> [[淤泥|淤泥]]（污水排放带来的[[沉积物|沉积物]]）也会污染水体。

